comment:
Thank you for moving with me, in this way, during this time. I truly believe that through our regular exploration together we can find healing and create meaningful change inside ourselves and out in our communities. 

No doubt you are getting stronger and more curious as we move along. Let’s keep going. 

Let me know how it’s going YALL!

Day 19. 02/28/2022 2:50 pm PHT. Last day of February and I'm still on day 19. Having an on and off relationship with yoga but still, I keep coming back and soon, I hope, that I can do this everyday :)

Guys, I could use some help. I am very new to yoga and I have trouble with the poses as it is, but what makes it even more harder is that I keep on slipping on my mat! I have sweaty hands and feet :/ this is why downward facing dog is a nightmare for me, I keep on sliding away or even collapsing down. I do have to admit that I am overweight, which does not help, and also that my mat was very cheap...I don't know if there's an actual difference between mats? Any advice??  Thank you in advance and sorry for any spelling mistakes, English is not my first language.

Hey girl! 
(Cause I feel like I know you) I began this journey on New Years with intentions of finishing with folks who began then too. Well life happens and so do Covid surges lol. I’m a burnt out RN and sometimes don’t fell like working out. No matter how relaxing yoga makes my muscles feel. Some days I rather lay on the couch, in front of TV and not think. Know what I mean. But I always come back to yoga! Self cares yo! Your soothing voice and lighthearted humor brighten my spirits. Today was day 19, just barely managing to getter dunnnn. I feel better and ready for bed. Thank you for your dedication. Otherwise I would be sitting on the cough right now, watching mindless reruns… Know any series I can binge? Haha. JKJK! God bless you and little Benji!
Thanks Adriene for your great work, i really appreciate the yoga you offer. We have ice and sleet out there and this is great therapy. Thanks.
OMG one of my favorites. I feel strong, open and ready. <3

When I started this yoga journey I didn't miss a single day, I was so proud of myself because no matter how tired or busy I was I somehow found time to honor my commitment to this journey. Until day 19. Then I got covid and it all went downhill from there. I went through so much stress and sadness but I finally recovered and remembered a promise to myself to get back on the mat and continue practicing. I felt weak and as if I had lost all progress, but I feel so much better now that I have completed Day 19 and I am back on track. Yoga With Adriene is a true blessing, I am so grateful❤
Thank you so much 💓
Did not regret being present again Adriene, thanks!

Day 19 ✅ I love the stretches on this one today. I have been feeling achy due to pms and just a general malaise. I loved how I had to hold the side stretch, I always feel that I release some weight when I do that. I feel so relieved and relaxed in my muscles when I do that. I am getting ready for that irritable and moody phase of my moon cycle and these daily practices are helping me so much to just calm my emotions down. Thank you Adriene and Benji! 💖💜💙💚💛🧡❤
Nice session.
day 19 and I notice the changes. Thanks so much @adriene
Hi. Is anyone else doing Move through February after enjoying it so much through January? Loving it the second time around. 💜 Sue, New Forest, UK xx🙏
Thanks a bunch. You are a true gem!
Thank you🤗Namaste🙏
PUMPED!

I am way behind, but working through the days one at a time.  I have finally completed day 19 (2/17/22)  and am determined to finish.  
This practice has been very helpful to me this year, in ways I didn't expect.  On an emotional level, I feel the breath work helping me manage strong feelings.  I'm working on speaking boundaries when they are needed rather than gathering tension until it explodes. On a physical level, I finally feel like I know how to engage my abs (after all these years!!) and it has made my other forms of exercise much more focused and beneficial.  
Grateful for the Move challenge and the YWA community. Namaste.
This is becoming a necessity. Amazing 😍
Day 19 DONEEE

Merci for all Adriene what would we do without you !!!💚

(it's my first time following a yoga programme)

Amazing yoga journey, special Thankyou to Adriene and everyone around the world to support each other

I'm trying, planning, and hoping to be able to do yoga daily for a long time after I finish this journey, whether it being one session, half a session, or multiple. I keep forgetting that it actually helps me. So, future-me, here is your reminder!
awesome, thank you!

Day 19 completed

maybe I messed up this journey, skipping days and be late by one day then two days but even that happens this month was a great move to me I spent the first 15 days asking myself what I am moving forward and there's no answer. But now I realise that I want to move closer towards me! exams has been tough little but this few minutes makes me think about how to nourishing myself everyday, I didn't succeed in not skipping days but the day I've done makes my mental health more good. I get more organised, built new habits, getting stronger learn how to enjoy whatever I do! maybe in April or another month I will try to repeat this journey in better way but All of you, make sure that this journey is your comfort zone not a compatition or any kind of stress but to put yourself first! give it a time to think about You!

I'm a couple days behind, but I'm glad I came. I'm having the same issue I had last journey, which is that my shoulder ligaments are very lax and they don't like downward facing dog. Have to go back to physical therapy if I want to do that pose with y'all, but checking in with my body every day is helping a lot. Discovering limitations is part of the journey, and hopefully learning how to adapt my behavior in order to accomodate those limitations will be the result of my journey this time. Thanks Adrienne, and good job friends! - a very tired x-ray tech.

Woah. Usually, during the days where the practice is 'hard' and quick-paced, I have trouble keeping up. I have to frequently pause the video, or rewind it a bit. Sometimes I find that Adriene already went through two poses and I'm still transitioning to one 😂😂 My hands are sweaty, too, and I often have to pause to wipe them dry. Often, it makes me feel frustrated. 

BUT TODAY, WOAH! I'm having a mild fever today and stomach pain, yet I went through the whole practice without pausing or rewinding. I was able to stay through the extended side angles aka the 'hard, foundational poses.' 😉 It was amazing-- at some points I was like, "Woah, I did THAT?"

Really found room for exploration today, indeed! 😊 I can't believe just 19 days or practice has already done so much. Sending love and power to those practicing, today! Namaste ❤
Beautiful 😍
beautiful side body openings and spaciousness sensations for me.  bless you 💕Adrienne and Benji baby🐾

I am rehabbing from a sever break in my ankle.  After with two surgeries, terrible bone infections, a fall off my dang scooter and re-injury when I got too confident and the wheel caught on a tiny pebble tracked in on the floor...grrrrr.  Coming up on two years later I'm only in episodic pain and can walk with almost no limp.  But I never thought I'd be able to sit cross legged again.  

Then I could do that and while it was doubtful I would be able to cross them the opposite way I was so glad.  Then I could do that, but I would probably never be able to sit back on my toes either curled under OR with the tops of my feet flat.  Then I could but never for very long.  Now I can do it for much longer and it even feels good!  

Will I ever be able to do tree poses and maintain my balance again?  Will I ever be able to do a deep Asian style squat and keep my balance?  My balance is way off because of the atrophy in muscles in my feet, core, hips and legs that have atrophied for almost two years... My ankle doesn't bend all the way like that anymore.  Or will it...with gentle patience...in time?  I don't know but I'm feeling stronger and more flexible with each passing day and am feeling SO much better in my body.  I am grateful Adrian.  Thank you.  Namaste'

Almost one year ago, after the first 30 day journey we did with Adrienne, we were in a state of reflective turmoil. One of us had lost our job due to downsizing and we decided to start investing in ourselves by rekindling old passions and hobbies. From there, we decided to start a youtube channel to share videos we were creating for our anxious son to calm him and to use as sleep aids. We found a passion and a community and began finding ourselves smiling much more often. Today, our channel hit 10K subs and we cannot believe it. This confidence, this drive to push ourselves, came from a simple choice to try after doing 30 straight days of yoga with you! We are so grateful and love the self-assurance and inner peace yoga and meditation has brought to our lives. Life is too short not to explore your potential and your passions. Thank you for this wonderful gift Adrienne. Like many of the people here, you touched our lives in a way you cannot even imagine. Peace & Positivity Always ☮💟☮💟☮💟

Today my body feels sore and my spirit was tired, although I woke up feeling more refreshed because I was able to get more sleep. I allowed myself to take breaks this time around, and really listened to the voice inside me that was saying to not push it today. I think in all my efforts to make space in my shoulders, I was actually tensing them and pushing them away from my ears with too much effort! So today's emphasis of exploration for me was to see how I can move in every pose with relaxed shoulders. It caused my face, that often gets a little scrunched up in my focusing, to easily relax along with it. It was different, and I feel that I didn't go "all in" to each of the poses, but I at least attempted every pose, and I'm trying to accept this as okay and wonderful.

I cannot move as fast as Adriene from one pose to the next. When I try that, it hurts. 2. Move at my own pace (again to not get hurt). Often I’m getting into a position and she’s already moved on to something else. That’s okay. Go at my pace. 3. This is not a competition. I’m learning something I’ve never done before.

Ah, today I realize that different parts of us are in different stages and comfort level, not just physically, but also mentally. I focused on exploring what and how today’s movement felt like and got the insight how my left side was far more hesitant und less energized than the right side. And looking now back, that’s us in daily life. Some parts take more time or temporary are harder to move. We are so complex, it’s really important to understand the duality and complexity of ourselves. It’s okay to want to do things, but to struggle with moving ourselves in some areas. That was so interesting today, what an insight that there is so much to move and how we can have all different states of comfort and hesitation in all areas. Moving on, moving towards what we are and want, is a complex, but very rewarding process. It really needs a lot of compassion and consistency.
